  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\nAfter a considerable amount of effort, I finally stumbled upon `quarkus.arc.context-propagation.enabled` while broswing through the code, and it seems to have resolved my problem. I must admit, I was surprised to find that this configuration is not mentioned in the official documentation at https://quarkus.io/guides/context-propagation. As a result, I'm still uncertain about the full implications of setting it to false, which in turn requires a more extensive testing process to ensure everything continues to function as expected.\r\n\r\nMy use case for disabling `quarkus.arc.context-propagation.enabled` is that I require a new request scope when executing a uni subscriber on a different thread asynchoniously. By doing so, I can detach from the original request scope without losing crucial tenant context information.\r\n\r\nTherefore, I propose enhancing the existing guide on [CONTEXT PROPAGATION IN QUARKUS](https://quarkus.io/guides/context-propagation) to include detailed information about the `quarkus.arc.context-propagation.enabled` property and its effects when both enabled and disabled. With this addition, the mechanisms of the context propagation will become more accessible and developers are enabled to adjust the context propagation settings more effectively.",
